 to a practical and realworld solution the award supports those aiming to achieve measurable social impact  the kuno awardee is provided with 00 in funding  award recipients are visionaries with deep domain expertise in fields relating to the specific st century challenges addressed by their project or venture which may become a forprofit business or nonprofit organization part of an academic institution etc    applications are now open please click here to begin the application process  purpose as part of sr foundation’s mission to support talented individuals with great potential and high aspirations in the arts sciences and social entrepreneurship especially those furthering international cultural collaboration sr foundation provides intervention and support to social entrepreneurs early in their formation this may be through investment or grant funding   eligibility requirements     applicant must be at early or midcareer and possess a phd in a relevant field     project must be the original idea of the applicant or the applicant’s team     project must be in a startup phase to be considered a startup the project may not have been organized or may have been in operation for up to but no longer than two years      applicants must commit  of their time minimum twenty hours per week to the projectorganizations development for the duration of the year oct  sept        projects led by two individuals may apply both partners must meet all eligibility requirements and make a  time commitment of no fewer than twenty hours per week to the development of the venture     applicant must be associated with a college university or other type of educational institution described in section c of the internal revenue code and classified as a public charity under section 9a    applicant must commit to project timeline as stated here october  september   – year for the project march   – project interim report due  september   – final report due october  – october   – final report presentation hosted by sr foundation – date to be determined by sr  note project can take the form of scientific research forprofit nonprofit or undecided as long as their core mission is to create impact for the social good and consistent to sr foundation’s charitable purpose selection process august   project submissions are due submit through application portal here september   finalist informed september   finalist deadline to confirm acceptance september   kuno award winner announced october   project year begins awardees will be selected by the board of directors of sr foundation selection criteria prospective applicants could come from a vast field of backgrounds as long as they have compelling ideas and are dedicated leaders they will be judged on entrepreneurial leadership the scalable model of their ideas andor ventures and the sustainable impact of their ideas andor ventures  previous winners see all winners dr sheila ohlsson walker products  adsr  en products  adsr washington award  sr foundation skip to main content search form search login news toggle navigation washington award since its inception in 00 the washington award has recognized talented artists in the fields of music dance and visual arts especially those who contribute to international cultural collaboration each winner is awarded a cash prize of  in addition the awards committee may designate a grand prize winner who receives an additional  award winners are honored annually in the spring at the washington awards ceremony applications are now open until october   please click here to begin the application process  please thoroughly read the eligibility requirements terms  conditions and faq page before beginning the application process the  winners are grand prizewinning composer saad haddad and washington award winners maggie finnegan soprano gilad hochman composer karen ouzounian cello and seeta patel dance each of these forwardthinking artists is pushing the boundaries of their artistic and performance practices to learn more about the  winners click here previous winners see all winners karen ouzounian cello moto osada composer tadao arimoto design shizuo kuwahara conductor ryu goto violin award selection committee jenny bilfield president and ceo washington performing arts michael djupstrom pianist composer and winner of the sr washington award grand prize 0 robert dwyer partner dorsey  whitney llp diane kanca partner voutelohrfink magro  mcandrew llp philip kennicott art and architecture critic the washington post jason moran jazz pianist composer educator and artistic director for jazz kennedy center klaus ottmann deputy director for curatorial and academic affairs the phillips collection caitlin teal price photography artist board of directors  sr foundation skip to main content search form search login news toggle navigation board of directors sachiko kuno phd president  ceo dr sachiko kuno studied biochemistry and biochemical engineering as one of a few japanese female scientists she obtained her phd in biochemical engineering from kyoto university japan and has conducted postdoctoral research at the technical university of munich germany in the mid0s dr kuno joined her research partner dr ryuji ueno and established rtech ueno ltd in japan to commercialize prostones a class of functional fatty acids whose therapeutic potential was first identified by dr ueno leading teams of talented scientists drs ueno and kuno unlocked the therapeutic potential of prostones leading to more than  patents and patent applications successful launch of rescula® eye drops the first bioactive lipid ever used to treat glaucoma in japan dr sachiko kuno studied biochemistry and biochemical engineering as one of a few japanese female scientists she obtained her phd in biochemical engineering from kyoto university japan and has conducted postdoctoral research at the technical university of munich germany in the mid0s dr kuno joined her research partner dr ryuji ueno and established rtech ueno ltd in japan to commercialize prostones a class of functional fatty acids whose therapeutic potential was first identified by dr ueno leading teams of talented scientists drs ueno and kuno unlocked the therapeutic potential of prostones leading to more than  patents and patent applications successful launch of rescula® eye drops the first bioactive lipid ever used to treat glaucoma in japan leveraging rtech’s success in japan the two moved to bethesda md and established sucampo group an affiliation of companies in the americas asia and europe dr kuno was sucampo group’s founding ceo and chair of the board until she stepped down in 0 during her time at sucampo dr kuno conducted research and development the operation of the company and the successful launch of the drs’ second product amitiza® for the treatment of chronic idiopathic constipation in adults irritable bowel syndrome with constipation and opioidinduced constipation in adults sucampo which acquired rtech ueno in 0 is listed and traded on nasdaq in 0 she cofounded vlp therapeutics llc to combat st century global public health problems through revolutionary iαvlp technology dr kuno currently serves as the president and ceo of sr foundation in washington dc a c nonprofit organization she cofounded in  to support talented individuals with high aspirations and great potential in the arts sciences and social entrepreneurship especially those who are furthering international cultural collaboration in  dr kuno cofounded we capital a femaleled investment fund in washington dc an impact investment group we capital invests in female leadership while promoting social impact and financial returns she is also a founding member of the greater washington partnership a group of civicminded business leaders committed to improving the greater washington region dr kuno is the cofounder and visionary creative behind halcyon launched in  and its mission to catalyze and nurture emerging creatives striving for a better world driven by dr kuno’s vision halcyon’s family of innovative programs including the acclaimed halcyon incubator is growing rapidly to include halcyon stage a pioneering creatives series of performances and conversations halcyon arts lab a residency based studio arts program and halcyon dialogue a series of highlevel discussions among global experts focusing on major topics including implications of robots for global society and social impactbased sciences she currently serves on the board of trustees for johns hopkins medicine on the board of directors for the maureen and mike mansfield foundation and on the advisory board of this for diplomats at meridian international center dr kuno has received several awards over the years including the ernst and young entrepreneur of the year award for the greater washington area in the life sciences category 00 and recognition as one of the  “women who mean business” by the washington business journal 009 she has also been named in forbes magazine’s top  america’s richest self made women 0 and the world’s 00 most powerful women by forbes japan 0 most recently dr kuno was awarded stateswoman of the year  by the harvard business school of japan and received the avon awards to women  current positions cofounder  managing member sr technology holdings llc bethesda maryland cofounder  board of directors rusk intellectual reserve ag zug switzerland cofounder president  ceo sr foundation washington dc cofounder we capital washington dc  cofounder  founding board member halcyon washington dc  founding member greater washington partnership specially appointed professor graduate school of advanced integrated studies in human survivability kyoto university board of trustees johns hopkins medicine baltimore maryland board of trustees federal city council board of directors the maureen and mike mansfield foundation washington dc advisory board member this for diplomats at meridian international center washington dc advisory board member naisa global read more marianne f chaconas vice president marianne chaconas a native washingtonian brings a broad range of experiences and skills to sr ms chaconas’ multifaceted background includes marketing and business management experience in the private industry in the areas of telecommunications aerospace government contracting and real estate and in the federal government with the us treasury and department of defense she comes to sr with a great appreciation for the arts especially fine arts and dance marianne chaconas a native washingtonian brings a broad range of experiences and skills to sr ms chaconas’ multifaceted background includes marketing and business management experience in the private industry in the areas of telecommunications aerospace government contracting and real estate and in the federal government with the us treasury and department of defense her telecommunications experience was enhanced as a member of the first technical and managerial training program for selected graduate degreed staff members her experience in contracts and contracts administration was gained while working for government contractors and the government where she also refined her skills as a program manager and analyst her management skills were further honed in the government as a branch manager within all areas of logistics management where her responsibilities included trouble shooting functional and personnel issues as a member of a special staff group marianne helped develop and implement an executive performance information measurement system to include an automated input and reporting system covering an entire government agency ms chaconas currently runs her own real estate management business ms chaconas received her bachelor’s degree in business administration from mount vernon college and her masters of business administration in international business from the george washington university included among her scholastic achievements is membership in beta gamma sigma an international business honor society ms chaconas is a selfproclaimed animal lover and supports several proanimal efforts including serving for many years as a virginia state council member for the humane society of the united states hsus she comes to sr with a great appreciation for the arts especially fine arts and dance read more douglas w charnas secretarytreasurer douglas w charnas is a washington dc lawyer who has represented nonprofit organizations since 9 when he left the office of chief counsel for the internal revenue service to enter private practice he has worked with sr foundation since its formation in  and is currently a member of the board of directors and the secretarytreasurer in addition to his love of music mr charnas has a passion for antique and sports cars douglas w charnas is a washington dc lawyer who has represented nonprofit organizations since 9 when he left the office of chief counsel for the internal revenue service to enter private practice he has worked with sr foundation since its formation in  and is currently a member of the board of directors and the secretarytreasurer mr charnas worked on the formation and implementation of the martin luther king jr federal holiday commission which was established by congress in 9 to encourage the observance of dr king’s birthday he is a founding board member of the europeanamerican cultural foundation and also serves as its secretarytreasurer currently he serves as an officer in other nonprofit organizations including as secretarytreasurer of the j edgar murdock inn of court at the united states tax court mr charnas is a partner in the law firm of mcguirewoods llp where his practice focuses on tax and corporate law he is also an adjunct professor at georgetown law school in addition to his love of music in a wide range of genres mr charnas has a passion for antique and sports cars read more ueno award  sr foundation skip to main content search form search login news toggle navigation ueno award sr foundation established the ryuji ueno award for ion channels or barrier function research commonly known as the “ueno award” in partnership with the american physiological society aps in 00  the ueno award is given annually to an individual demonstrating outstanding promise based on hisher research in ion channels or epithelial barrier function in 0 sr foundation renewed its collaboration with aps to present the ueno award with a variation in focus until 00 the award will be presented to an early career investigator demonstrating outstanding promise based on hisher research in wound healing tissue remodeling andor organ regeneration note deadline november   apply here previous winners see all winners my helms phd assistant professor physiology baljit s khakh phd associate professor pharmacology christopher weber md phd assistant professor pathology declan mccole phd assistant professor akira sawa md phd professor psychiatry user account  sr foundation skip to main content search form search login news toggle navigation user account primary tabscreate new account log inactive tab request new password email or username  password  log in founders  sr foundation skip to main content search form search login news toggle navigation founders sachiko kuno phd president  ceo dr sachiko kuno studied biochemistry and biochemical engineering as one of a few japanese female scientists she obtained her phd in biochemical engineering from kyoto university japan and has conducted postdoctoral research at the technical university of munich germany in the mid0s dr kuno joined her research partner dr ryuji ueno and established rtech ueno ltd in japan to commercialize prostones a class of functional fatty acids whose therapeutic potential was first identified by dr ueno leading teams of talented scientists drs ueno and kuno unlocked the therapeutic potential of prostones leading to more than  patents and patent applications successful launch of rescula® e